    "text": "配信をご覧いただいた皆さんいかがだったでしょう?"
  },
  {
    "id": 49,
    "text": "ちょっとコメントも見ようか。"
  },
  {
    "id": 50,
    "text": "。"
  },
  {
    "id": 51,
    "text": "大沼パセリさんのMVと25の2D雰囲気違ってどっちも良かっ。"
  },
  {
    "id": 52,
    "text": "そうなんです。"
  },
  {
    "id": 53,
    "text": "こう瑞希、なんかこうなんて言うん。"
  },
  {
    "id": 54,
    "text": "、学生が進路とか、まもなくプロセカも5周年を迎えます、"
  },
  {
    "id": 55,
    "text": "5周年に向けて色々あった瑞希です、その中で前を向け、"
  },
  {
    "id": 56,
    "text": "前を向くのにはこういうことがあっ、でも私は、"
  },
  {
    "id": 57,
    "text": "みたい、私、僕は頑張ろうっていう気持ちをなんかそう描写し、"
  },
  {
    "id": 58,
    "text": "なんか25の気持ちみたいな感じの飾ってになってると思うんですけど大沼さんの方、"
  },
  {
    "id": 59,
    "text": "、なんて言う。"
  },
  {
    "id": 60,
    "text": "社会人で疲れてる子、、それでも頑張って前を向いていこうって自分を鼓舞してるみたいなMVなってっ、"
  },
  {
    "id": 61,
    "text": "私はなんか歌詞は歌詞でも歌い手と、歌ってる側と、"
  },
  {
    "id": 62,
    "text": "表現の仕方によって曲自体、、幅がすごい広い楽曲なんだ、"
  },
  {
    "id": 63,
    "text": "飾ってって思ったの、、是非、、大沼さんの方の、"
  },
  {
    "id": 64,
    "text": "2Dって言うんだろう、あれ。"
  },
  {
    "id": 65,
    "text": "なんて言うん。"
  },
  {
    "id": 66,
    "text": "MVというんですか。"
  },
  {
    "id": 67,
    "text": "MVも合わせて楽しんでいただけたらいいなと私は思いまし。"
  },
  {
    "id": 68,
    "text": "、改めて、いいベストで言う、なんか結構これまで25全体的になんかこう重ためというかこう息がしにくい部分が露呈、"
  },
  {
    "id": 69,
    "text": "露見する、ストーリーが多かったと思うんですけど1番なんかこう高校2年生だったりとか、"
  },
  {
    "id": 70,
    "text": "、高校12年生からもそうだ、、3年、高校生が等身大で共感ができるストーリーになっているのではないかなと私は思うイベントストーリーになっているので、"
  },
  {
    "id": 71,
    "text": "あの進路の決め方とか、"
  },
  {
    "id": 72,
    "text": "自分の好きを認めてあげることに自信がなかったりとか自分の好きなものを愛してあげられないん、"
  },
  {
    "id": 73,
    "text": "今はっていう子がもしい、それは学生だけじゃなくて社会人の方ももちろんです、"
  },
  {
    "id": 74,
    "text": "是非イベントストーリーまだ見れていない方だっ、楽曲に触れられていない方がい、"
  },
  {
    "id": 75,
    "text": "何か、もしかしたら心に残る言葉みたいなものは今の自分だからこそあるストーリーと楽曲になっていると思うの、"
  },
  {
    "id": 76,
    "text": "、、大人の皆さん、学生の皆さんも最後まで余す所なく楽しんでいただけたらいいなと私は思い。"
  },
  {
    "id": 77,
    "text": "、ということで、、イベントほどけぬ明日に手を伸ばしてのストーリーをまだ見終わってないっていう方、"
  },
  {
    "id": 78,
    "text": "次のイベントが始まっ、ストーリーのイベントストーリーから全て読むことをはできますの、"
  },
  {
    "id": 79,
    "text": "是非読んで。"
  }
]

response_parts.content:
{
  "response": [
    {
      "id": 0,
      "translated": "I'd like to watch the MV for \"Kazaite\" and talk a bit about the song."
    },
    {
      "id": 1,
      "translated": "But before we watch the 3DMV, I have a comment from the Sega 3DMV production team to share with you."
    },
    {
      "id": 2,
      "translated": "They said, \"In the 3DMV for Kazaite, we used the visual of falling into water to represent Mizuki's wavering emotions"
    },
    {
      "id": 3,
      "translated": "and their inability to be honest with the other members. We used the insert function and spent a lot of time"
    },
    {
      "id": 4,
      "translated": "on the underwater falling sequence through a process of trial and error."
    },
    {
      "id": 5,
      "translated": "While there are still challenges in fully depicting emotional depth,"
    },
    {
      "id": 6,
      "translated": "we hope you enjoy this new form of expression through Mizuki.\""
    },
    {
      "id": 7,
      "translated": "Alright, let's take a look at the 3DMV right away."
    },
    {
      "id": 8,
      "translated": "..."
    },
    {
      "id": 9,
      "translated": "Did you see that expression just now?"
    },
    {
      "id": 10,
      "translated": "They're smiling."
    },
    {
      "id": 11,
      "translated": "It's so good."
    },
    {
      "id": 12,
      "translated": "Wow."
    },
    {
      "id": 13,
      "translated": "I was honestly blown away when I first saw this 3DMV."
    },
    {
      "id": 14,
      "translated": "I couldn't believe"
    },
    {
      "id": 15,
      "translated": "how much the scenery changes."
    },
    {
      "id": 16,
      "translated": "It goes from a school-like setting to an after-school vibe, with shots through windows showing leaves,"
    },
    {
      "id": 17,
      "translated": "and when they're walking down the hallway, you can see things in the light..."
    },
    {
      "id": 18,
      "translated": "Not Wi-Fi, but... what do you call it? Like dust motes or particles floating in the air."
    },
    {
      "id": 19,
      "translated": "The direction is so detailed."
    },
    {
      "id": 20,
      "translated": "I was wondering how they even did that."
    },
    {
      "id": 21,
      "translated": "It was amazing."
    },
    {
      "id": 22,
      "translated": "The way the camera circles around and the characters swap out..."
    },
    {
      "id": 23,
      "translated": "The production value was so high, it really surprised me."
    },
    {
      "id": 24,
      "translated": "It was just so good."
    },
    {
      "id": 25,
      "translated": "I'm glad we could look back on it."
    },
    {
      "id": 26,
      "translated": "The 2DMV is also incredible, I've watched it so many times."
    },
    {
      "id": 27,
      "translated": "Regarding the 2DMV, this is just my personal take,"
    },
    {
      "id": 28,
      "translated": "since nothing has been explicitly stated and I haven't heard the details yet,"
    },
    {
      "id": 29,
      "translated": "but the 2DMV has a setting that looks like a birthday party, with a seat of honor."
    },
    {
      "id": 30,
      "translated": "Mizuki is there by a cake, and the camera pans over things that symbolize what Mizuki is \"adorning\" themselves with."
    },
    {
      "id": 31,
      "translated": "Like the letter from their older sister,"
    },
    {
      "id": 32,
      "translated": "and ribbons... seeing those things in the 2D version was really wonderful."
    },
    {
      "id": 33,
      "translated": "Both versions were amazing."
    },
    {
      "id": 34,
      "translated": "The sheer amount of information in them is staggering."
    },
    {
      "id": 35,
      "translated": "As for the song, I felt that Mizuki's previous songs often had a lot of painful lyrics."
    },
    {
      "id": 36,
      "translated": "I'm not trying to compare it to past songs, but I really felt this one has a lot of forward-looking lyrics."
    },
    {
      "id": 37,
      "translated": "Even so, it still captures those wavering emotions inside Mizuki."
    },
    {
      "id": 38,
      "translated": "I don't think Mizuki is someone who can just let everything out."
    },
    {
      "id": 39,
      "translated": "So I consulted with the director about the nuances, like how much"
    },
    {
      "id": 40,
      "translated": "strength to add or subtract. We talked a lot while creating this song."
    },
    {
      "id": 41,
      "translated": "There are parts where the audio sounds like a radio, and I asked,"
    },
    {
      "id": 42,
      "translated": "\"Instead of just putting the emotion out there, can I try making my voice sound a bit raspy?\""
    },
    {
      "id": 43,
      "translated": "We discussed a lot of those subtle nuances during the recording."
    },
    {
      "id": 44,
      "translated": "I hope you'll enjoy both the full 2DMV and the 3DMV where Mizuki smiles at us."
    },
    {
      "id": 45,
      "translated": "Both are already uploaded to the official ProSeka YouTube channel,"
    },
    {
      "id": 46,
      "translated": "so please go check them out."
    },
    {
      "id": 47,
      "translated": "And with that, our short time together is coming to an end. This concludes the ProSeka AfterTalk for the \"Reaching Out for an Unbreakable Tomorrow\" edition."
    },
    {
      "id": 48,
      "translated": "To everyone watching the stream, how did you like it?"
    },
    {
      "id": 49,
      "translated": "Let's take a quick look at the comments."
    },
    {
      "id": 50,
      "translated": "..."
    },
    {
      "id": 51,
      "translated": "Someone said, \"Onuma Parsley's MV and the Niigo 2D version have different vibes, and both are great.\""
    },
    {
      "id": 52,
      "translated": "That's so true."
    },
    {
      "id": 53,
      "translated": "For Mizuki... how should I put it?"
    },
    {
      "id": 54,
      "translated": "Students thinking about their future... and ProSeka is also approaching its 5th anniversary."
    },
    {
      "id": 55,
      "translated": "Mizuki has been through a lot leading up to this 5th anniversary, and in the midst of that, they're looking forward."
    },
    {
      "id": 56,
      "translated": "It shows that while things happened, they're still thinking,"
    },
    {
      "id": 57,
      "translated": "\"I'm going to do my best!\" I think \"Kazaite\" depicts those Niigo-like feelings."
    },
    {
      "id": 58,
      "translated": "But in Onuma-san's version,"
    },
    {
      "id": 59,
      "translated": "how do I describe it?"
    },
    {
      "id": 60,
      "translated": "It's like a working adult who's tired, but still trying to encourage themselves to keep moving forward."
    },
    {
      "id": 61,
      "translated": "I felt that depending on the singer and the way it's expressed,"
    },
    {
      "id": 62,
      "translated": "the song itself has a huge range."
    },
    {
      "id": 63,
      "translated": "I really felt that with \"Kazaite.\" Please check out Onuma-san's..."
    },
    {
      "id": 64,
      "translated": "Is it called a 2D version? What would you call it?"
    },
    {
      "id": 65,
      "translated": "How should I say it?"
    },
    {
      "id": 66,
      "translated": "The original MV?"
    },
    {
      "id": 67,
      "translated": "I hope you'll enjoy that MV as well."
    },
    {
      "id": 68,
      "translated": "Looking back, a lot of Niigo stories have been quite heavy or felt a bit suffocating."
    },
    {
      "id": 69,
      "translated": "But this time, I think it's a story that high schoolers"
    },
    {
      "id": 70,
      "translated": "can really relate to on a personal level. It's a very down-to-earth event story."
    },
    {
      "id": 71,
      "translated": "Things like deciding on a career path,"
    },
    {
      "id": 72,
      "translated": "lacking the confidence to acknowledge what you like, or not being able to love the things you love..."
    },
    {
      "id": 73,
      "translated": "If there's anyone feeling that way right now, whether you're a student or a working adult,"
    },
    {
      "id": 74,
      "translated": "and you haven't seen the event story or heard the song yet,"
    },
    {
      "id": 75,
      "translated": "I think there are words in this story and song that will really resonate with you because of who you are now."
    },
    {
      "id": 76,
      "translated": "I hope everyone, both adults and students, will enjoy it to the very end."
    },
    {
      "id": 77,
      "translated": "So, for those who haven't finished the story for \"Reaching Out for an Unbreakable Tomorrow\" yet,"
    },
    {
      "id": 78,
      "translated": "even after the next event starts, you can still read the whole story from the archives."
    },
    {
      "id": 79,
      "translated": "Please give it a read."
    }
  ]
}

